18/05/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Serbian Justice Minister Snezana Malovic was in Zagreb on Monday (May 17th) where she signed a memorandum of understanding in the fight against corruption. In doing so, Serbia joined the Regional Anti-Corruption Initiative, which aims to promote co-operation in the fight against graft. Malovic and Croatian counterpart Ivan Simonovic also announced agreement on a document covering the extradition of those suspected of corruption and organised crime. It will be signed once Zagreb lifts its ban on extraditions. (Beta, RTS, Jutarnji List, Tanjug, B92 - 17/05/10)
